==English==
===Etymology===
From Old Norse [[kjólr]].
===Noun===
'''keel''' (''plural:'' '''keels''')

#A large beam along the [[underside]] of a [[ship]]'s [[hull]] from [[bow]] to [[stern]].
#Sometimes, a rigid, flat piece of material [[anchor]]ed to the lowest part of the hull of a [[ship]] to it greater control and [[stability]].

====Derived terms====
*[[keelhaul]] ''verb''
*[[keel over]] ''verb''

